cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a novel data modeling technology that can be applied to all types of signal or data, structured or unstructured, textual or not. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the application of the technology to e-Discovery and contextual navigation, which further supports the relevance of cs.IR and cs.AI.
